<![CDATA[<p class="MsoNormal" style=""><font face="arial">Hi {!Contact.FirstName},<br></font><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br>Further to our previous email, unfortunately, </span><b style="font-size: 12pt;">payment for your insurance cover remains outstanding</b><span style="font-size: 12pt;">.<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br><b>If we do not receive the outstanding payment before [insert date here] unfortunately we will have to cancel down your policy from inception.</b></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"> It will be your responsibility to get in contact with us before this date if you still require the policy.<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br><b>Please accept this as your 30 days’ notice, as per our terms and conditions, of your policy being cancelled due to non-payment.<br></b></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><b><br></b>Please contact us immediately so we can process a payment and ensure your cover remains in place.<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br>You can call us directly on </span><b style="font-size: 12pt;">01242 808740</b><span style="font-size: 12pt;">.<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br>Kind regards,<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br>{!User.FirstName}<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Customer Accounts Team<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br>E: customersupport@kingsbridge.co.uk<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">T: 01242 808 740</span></p>]]></td>
</tr>
